name: Collection Ctenophora SMF
description: The Ctenophora collection is part of the SeSAMcollections of Senckenberg which combines all collectionsheld at the Senckenberg Natutal HistoryMuseum of Frankfurt. This collection iscomparatively small; the material reflects not onlythe research activities of our institutein the ArcticOcean and North Sea, but also in the Mediterranean and Red Sea. There are no types present today.
